<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">Arrows Asunder</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Big Yoda</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">A standard deck which uses “worthless” rares that never come out from your trade folder. Do all those fun things you read about but never normally achieve, make Old Noser STR 42, discard the Witch King, defeat the Cave Troll and Balrog in one turn.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Cards</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Starting<br />
Frodo, Reluctant Adventurer<br />
<!--182-->The One Ring, The Ruling Ring<br />
<!--874-->Merry, Friend to Sam<br />
Birchseed, Tall Statesman<br />
Smeagol, Old Noser<br />
<br />
<br />
Adventure Deck<br />
[1] Western <!--240-->Emyn Muil<br />
[2] Wold of Rohan<br />
[3] Golden Hall<br />
[4] White Mountains<br />
[5] Hornburg Courtyard<br />
[6] Hornburg <!--303-->Armory<br />
